6 An Act relating to Service Oklahoma; amending 47 O.S.
2021, Section 1104, as last amended by Section 18,
7 Chapter 330, O.S.L. 2025 (47 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section
1104), which relates to apportionment; amending,
8 merging, consolidating, and repealing multiple
versions of statute; modifying termination date of
9 certain apportionment; updating statutory language;
repealing 47 O.S. 2021, Section 1104, as last amended
10 by Section 7, Chapter 171, O.S.L. 2025 (47 O.S. Supp.
2025, Section 1104), which relates to apportionment;
11 and declaring an emergency.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 1104, as
16 last amended by Section 18, Chapter 330, O.S.L. 2025 (47 O.S. Supp.
17 2025, Section 1104), is amended to read as follows:
18 Section 1104. A. Unless otherwise provided by law, all fees,
19 taxes, and penalties collected or received pursuant to the Oklahoma
20 Vehicle License and Registration Act or Section 1-101 et seq. of
21 this title shall be apportioned and distributed monthly by the
22 Oklahoma Tax Commission Service Oklahoma in accordance with this
23 section. Service Oklahoma shall provide to the Oklahoma Tax
24 Commission monthly reports of motor vehicle collection information,
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1239 Page 1

1 incl uding, but not limited to, motor vehicle monthly apportionment
2 information, refunds, canceled vouchers, waste tire collections,
3 organ donor program amounts, driver license records, prorate
4 amounts, and sales tax amounts. The reports shall be delivered
5 electronically pursuant to the current calendar year apportionment
6 disbursement schedule provided to Service Oklahoma by the Oklahoma
7 Tax Commission on or before December 1st 1 annually.
8 One percent (1%) of the monies referred to in this section shall
9 be apportioned to the Licensed Operator Performance Fund created in
10 Section 3-106 of this title, in accordance with the applicable
11 metrics determined by Service Oklahoma.
